wiki.author: mieke.kriens@aqute.biz
wiki.text:
iText ® is a library that allows you to create and manipulate PDF documents. It enables developers looking to enhance web- and other applications with dynamic PDF document generation and/or manipulation.

Developers can use iText to:
* Serve PDF to a browser
* Generate dynamic documents from XML files or databases
* Use PDF's many interactive features
* Add bookmarks, page numbers, watermarks, etc.
* Split, concatenate, and manipulate PDF pages
* Automate filling out of PDF forms
* Add digital signatures to a PDF file

iText is available in Java as well as in C#.


### Source Control
* scm:git:https://github.com/weiyeh/iText-4.2.0.git (Users/Contributors)
* scm:git:https://github.com/weiyeh/iText-4.2.0.git (Developers)
* [scm:git:https://github.com/weiyeh/iText-4.2.0.git](scm:git:https://github.com/weiyeh/iText-4.2.0.git) (View)
